Doesn't matter that much because I suspect we're only ever dealing with a handful of types, but this can be optimized a little:
final var rdfTypeIds = new ArrayList<Long>(rdfTypes.size());
final var rdfTypeUris = new HashSet<String>();

for (final var type : results) {
    rdfTypeIds.add(type.getTypeId());
    rdfTypeUris.add(type.getTypeUri());
}

final var missingUris = rdfTypes.stream().map(URI::toString).filter(t -> !rdfTypeUris.contains(t)).collect(Collectors.toSet());

